The evidence with the title 'When a Catholic terrified the Heartland - The New York Times ' says Dec 10, 2011  ... By any measure, Alfred E. Smith, the Democratic candidate against Herbert C. Hoover in 1928, had a formidable record. Growing up  ... The school board of Daytona Beach, Fla., sent a note home with every student. It read simply:  ... If he is elected president, you will not be allowed to have or read a Bible. 
